since you got back, uh?

90
00:07:14,465 --> 00:07:15,350
All right.

91
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:16,949
Is it serious?

92
00:07:17,346 --> 00:07:18,421
It's a bar fight.

93
00:07:18,514 --> 00:07:20,214
But it's an off-duty cop
he whacked.

94
00:07:20,215 --> 00:07:21,589
He whacked a cop?

95
00:07:22,749 --> 00:07:24,118
Is the guy hurt?

96
00:07:24,119 --> 00:07:26,124
Well, Grandpa says he...

97
00:07:26,125 --> 00:07:27,354
"kicked the bull's ass...

98
00:07:27,355 --> 00:07:29,738
The length of the bar
and halfway down 10th Ave."

99
00:07:29,739 --> 00:07:31,225
When is he gonna to let up?

100
00:07:31,517 --> 00:07:32,938
Oh, Christ.

101
00:07:33,257 --> 00:07:34,179
Well...

102
00:07:34,491 --> 00:07:37,050
What the hell, it's nice
to know I have strong genes.

103
00:07:37,413 --> 00:07:39,956
Hope I'm getting pinched
for bar fights in my 60s.

104
00:07:39,957 --> 00:07:43,409
Just remember, Adam,
along with those strong genes...

105
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:46,598
My father passes on a lot
of other crap to go with it.

106
00:07:46,599 --> 00:07:49,558
- So stay away from him.
- He's not looking to hurt me.

107
00:07:49,559 --> 00:07:50,475
No, he's not.

108
00:07:50,781 --> 00:07:52,265
But it'll happen anyway.

109
00:07:52,758 --> 00:07:55,167
He'll spend the night in the can.
Fine with me.

110
00:07:57,766 --> 00:07:59,218
Lend me 800 dollars.

111
00:07:59,741 --> 00:08:00,495
Forget it.

112
00:08:00,496 --> 00:08:02,561
Last time I stood bail for him
was three years ago.

113
00:08:02,562 --> 00:08:03,796
I haven't heard from him since.

114
00:08:03,811 --> 00:08:06,062
I don't stand bail
for Jessie anymore.

115
00:08:06,063 --> 00:08:07,291
You're not standing bail.

116
00:08:07,292 --> 00:08:08,851
I'm borrowing the money.

117
00:08:09,444 --> 00:08:11,928
I've got 200, I'd like 800 more.

118
00:08:12,323 --> 00:08:13,436
So it's for you?

119
00:08:13,501 --> 00:08:14,254
Right!

120
00:08:22,924 --> 00:08:25,335
Adam, the last year
my mother was alive...

121
00:08:27,243 --> 00:08:29,177
I was 7 years old. Okay?

122
00:08:29,409 --> 00:08:32,776
Jessie took me along Christmas Eve
to buy a tree, right?

123
00:08:32,945 --> 00:08:36,225
Near midnight we're passing an
Esso station up near Riverdale...

124
00:08:36,226 --> 00:08:40,686
And right on top of the garage is
a perfect, all lit-up Christmas tree.

125
00:08:40,687 --> 00:08:45,583
So Jessie hits the brakes and he says,
"Wow, what a score, it's even got lights."

126
00:08:45,584 --> 00:08:46,915
Wait a minute.

127
00:08:47,244 --> 00:08:51,854
I'm standing lookout, I was 7 years old,
while he climbs up the drainpipe...

128
00:08:51,855 --> 00:08:54,363
And pulls down the tree,
lights and all.

129
00:08:54,390 --> 00:08:55,741
What's so funny?

130
00:08:55,853 --> 00:08:57,723
