what happened.

137
00:09:13,075 --> 00:09:14,983
Just know who you're
dealing with. All right?

138
00:09:14,984 --> 00:09:16,062
All right, all right.

139
00:09:21,980 --> 00:09:22,960
That's eight.

140
00:09:23,431 --> 00:09:24,348
Thanks.

141
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:30,659
That was nice what you did
in there... for them.

142
00:09:30,724 --> 00:09:32,885
They might get out of this
cesspool because of you.

143
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:34,839
Well, I had them over a barrel.

144
00:09:35,238 --> 00:09:38,517
Somebody loves you, you got a hell of
a weapon in the relationship, you know?

145
00:09:42,023 --> 00:09:43,230
Hey!

146
00:09:45,812 --> 00:09:48,508
Listen, it's supposed
to work both ways, kiddo.

147
00:09:48,650 --> 00:09:52,108
I mean, if you love somebody back,
then they got an equal weapon, no?

148
00:09:52,109 --> 00:09:54,526
You're right, pa.
I guess we got a standoff.

149
00:09:54,527 --> 00:09:57,703
- I guess we do.
- They may move. I think you did it.

150
00:09:57,704 --> 00:09:59,274
- I better get a cab.
- Good.

151
00:09:59,275 --> 00:10:00,447
How about dinner next week?

152
00:10:00,448 --> 00:10:02,588
Oh, sure. What time
should we be there?

153
00:10:03,723 --> 00:10:05,432
You did want Christine, no?

154
00:10:05,697 --> 00:10:06,867
Of course, Adam.

155
00:10:06,868 --> 00:10:10,370
You know Christine's always welcome.
You wanna catch a ride with us?

156
00:10:10,371 --> 00:10:12,965
- No, thanks.
- Okay, good night, Adam.

157
00:10:13,312 --> 00:10:15,666
- Bye, sweetheart.
