01:40:37,704 --> 01:40:39,802
They could have put me away
for 10 years.

1471
01:40:55,926 --> 01:40:57,670
Who got my charges reduced?

1472
01:40:58,170 --> 01:40:59,232
The charges?

1473
01:40:59,694 --> 01:41:00,498
Me!

1474
01:41:01,551 --> 01:41:05,513
I managed to squeeze a few lousy bucks
out of your Chinaman friend too.

1475
01:41:06,897 --> 01:41:08,153
I spent it, Adam...

1476
01:41:08,516 --> 01:41:09,671
Every nickel.

1477
01:41:10,403 --> 01:41:12,584
I thought about splitting
it with you, Adam.

1478
01:41:12,907 --> 01:41:13,913
I really did.

1479
01:41:15,227 --> 01:41:16,623
Then I thought...

1480
01:41:17,496 --> 01:41:19,427
If I'm gonna do the time...

1481
01:41:19,860 --> 01:41:22,549
Well, I have a little vigorish
coming to me.

1482
01:41:24,396 --> 01:41:25,334
So...

1483
01:41:26,528 --> 01:41:28,467
I figured the best thing was...

1484
01:41:29,332 --> 01:41:30,912
Just not to mention it.

1485
01:41:32,060 --> 01:41:33,717
Even Vito couldn't
argue with that.

1486
01:41:34,150 --> 01:41:35,302
Vito.

1487
01:41:36,139 --> 01:41:38,443
Vito... A lost cause.

1488
01:41:40,300 --> 01:41:41,693
From the beginning...

1489
01:41:42,415 --> 01:41:43,795
A lost cause.

1490
01:41:49,476 --> 01:41:51,177
You're your own man now...

1491
01:41:55,911 --> 01:41:57,675
Well, I'm out from under Vito.

1492
01:41:58,506 --> 01:41:59,730
Good.

1493
01:42:02,041 --> 01:42:04,112
You think you can get out
from under me?

1494
01:42:14,407 --> 01:42:16,323
No, Mom, I don't wanna talk to him.

1495
01:42:17,074 --> 01:42:18,706
No, just tell him that...

1496
01:42:19,239 --> 01:42:20,777
That Jessie is dying.

1497
01:42:21,683 --> 01:42:24,417
They're moving him from the infirmary
into the prison hospital.

1498
01:42:26,046 --> 01:42:27,456
Yeah, just tell him.

1499
01:42:27,859 --> 01:42:29,401
Okay, bye.

1500
01:42:38,928 --> 01:42:40,249
I'm looking...

1501
01:42:40,678 --> 01:42:42,237
Hi, I'm looking
for Jessie McMullen.

1502
01:42:42,914 --> 01:42:44,370
They just wheeled him
out of here.

1503
01:42:44,818 --> 01:42:45,725
Which way?

1504
01:42:45,751 --> 01:42:47,208
Won't do you no good.

1505
01:42:47,434 --> 01:42:48,761
Which way?!

1506
01:42:49,803 --> 01:42:52,870
Go back the way you came,
take the elevator to the basement.

1507
01:42:52,871 --> 01:42:53,785
Basement?

1508
01:42:54,232 --> 01:42:55,402
To the basement?

1509
01:43:01,148 --> 01:43:02,089
Hey!

1510
01:43:02,248 --> 01:43:03,700
Wait!

1511
01:43:04,322 --> 01:43:05,925
Is that Jessie McMullen?

1512
01:43:07,583 --> 01:43:08,487
Hey!

1513
01:43:09,363 --> 01:43:10,309
Please!

1514
01:43:10,480 --> 01:43:12,229
Wait a minute,
don't shut the door.

1515
01:43:49,043 --> 01:43:50,635
- Hi, Ma.
- Hello.

1516
01:43:50,873 --> 01:43:53,491
- So?
- So it's so big I can't find anything.

1517
01:43:53,500 --> 01:43:55,734
- Hi, Papa. Hi.
- Hi, Rose.

1518
01:43:55,735 --> 01:43:56,902
Thank you, Vito.

1519
01:43:56,903 --> 01:43:59,923
- My first time in your new house.
- I'm sorry about your father, Vito.

1520
01:44:00,412 --> 01:44:03,321
I know. Hey, who
have we got here?

1521
01:44:05,594 --> 01:44:07,134
Hiya, Nat.

1522
01:44:08,588 --> 01:44:10,305
It's all right, don't get up.

1523
01:44:17,957 --> 01:44:21,393
After 25 years, the shaygets
knows two Jewish words.

1524
01:44:21,394 --> 01:44:23,391
Well, you know.
Here, let me help you.

1525
01:44:34,941 --> 01:44:36,501
Time to let the angel in.

1526
01:44:36,949 --> 01:44:39,782
The angel won't have to squeeze
in under the chain.

1527
01:44:41,514 --> 01:44:44,751
I knew that was coming.
Your material is getting stale.

1528
01:44:48,229 --> 01:44:50,424
- Look who's here.
- Grandma.

1529
01:44:50,723 --> 01:44:54,024
I've been outside a half an hour waiting
for you to open the door for Elijah.

1530
01:45:14,948 --> 01:45:18,569
Anyway, they were thrilled that you
stopped by to see them.

1531
01:45:18,585 --> 01:45:22,387
Yeah, well, no reason to take
our problems out on them, huh?

1532
01:45:22,388 --> 01:45:24,697
Wait a minute, you gonna wait
for your mother to come down?

1533
01:45:25,525 --> 01:45:27,455
She'll be saying goodbye
for 20 minutes.

1534
01:45:28,962 --> 01:45:32,097
Plus, we'll just get in the same
old argument again.

1535
01:45:32,098 --> 01:45:33,725
What's the same old argument?

1536
01:45:35,872 --> 01:45:38,194
That everything you did,
you did for me.

1537
01:45:48,047 --> 01:45:51,647
If you hated the meat business
so much for 20 years...

1538
01:45:53,757 --> 01:45:56,358
Then I'm sorry, but stop blaming me.

1539
01:45:58,644 --> 01:46:00,271
You did it to yourself.

1540
01:46:10,123 --> 01:46:13,084
What's the most fun you've had
since you were a kid?

1541
01:46:15,542 --> 01:46:17,186
What's the most fun I've had?

1542
01:46:17,572 --> 01:46:19,131
Yeah, since you were a kid.

1543
01:46:22,615 --> 01:46:23,843
What?

1544
01:46:24,417 --> 01:46:25,631
The caper.

1545
01:46:25,952 --> 01:46:27,920
- The caper? The caper.
- Yeah.

1546
01:46:28,087 --> 01:46:29,428
Me too.

1547
01:46:31,893 --> 01:46:33,241
Oh, boy.

1548
01:46:34,148 --> 01:46:35,702
We are some family.

1549
01:46:40,355 --> 01:46:43,561
You know, the only time the three of us
ever had a drink together...

1550
01:46:43,851 --> 01:46:45,694
Was when we were
planning that robbery.

1551
01:46:49,833 --> 01:46:51,788
We are some family.

1552
01:46:57,050 --> 01:46:59,397
I brought back his ashes, Pop.

1553
01:47:01,988 --> 01:47:04,139
I thought that maybe the two of us...

1554
01:47:05,118 --> 01:47:07,366
Ought to bury him together.
Thank you.

1555
01:47:09,420 --> 01:47:10,545
Thank you.

1556
01:47:18,087 --> 01:47:20,146
You have any idea
what we ought to do with him?

1557
01:47:23,489 --> 01:47:24,959
Yes, I do.

1558
01:47:27,648 --> 01:47:29,616
So, what are you gonna do
with yourself now, Adam?

1559
01:47:29,642 --> 01:47:31,351
What do you want to
do with your life?

1560
01:47:34,883 --> 01:47:36,655
That's the first time
you ever asked me that.

1561
01:47:37,023 --> 01:47:38,333
- First time?
- Yeah.

1562
01:47:40,355 --> 01:47:42,686
All right, I'll ask
you a second time.

1563
01:47:42,752 --> 01:47:44,311
What do you wanna
do with your life?

1564
01:47:45,231 --> 01:47:46,975
Well, now that you ask me...

1565
01:47:48,357 --> 01:47:49,545
I don't know.

1566
01:47:50,970 --> 01:47:53,163
We lived in this building
when my mother died.

1567
01:47:54,858 --> 01:47:56,164
Right on that corner there...

1568
01:47:56,165 --> 01:47:58,334
Jessie pushed me into
my first fight.

1569
01:48:00,832 --> 01:48:02,514
It's his neighborhood, okay.

1570
01:48:12,064 --> 01:48:13,881
Okay, now lift.

1571
01:48:14,561 --> 01:48:16,545
You've got to be kidding.

1572
01:48:23,970 --> 01:48:26,271
- Where do you want this keg?
- All the way up.

1573
01:48:26,272 --> 01:48:27,873
This is an open-air service.

1574
01:48:27,878 --> 01:48:29,908
Here we go.

1575
01:48:29,909 --> 01:48:32,401
I thought I told you guys
to get light beer.

1576
01:48:34,245 --> 01:48:36,011
If I'd have known
this was a roof job...

1577
01:48:36,076 --> 01:48:37,722
I would have went
for wristwatches.

1578
01:48:55,401 --> 01:48:58,700
I know! I know the Church
approves of cremation.

1579
01:48:58,871 --> 01:49:02,574
But the Church also approves of playing
the guitar at the Mass these days.

1580
01:49:02,575 --> 01:49:05,738
Vito, over the side with him.

1581
01:49:06,446 --> 01:49:08,913
Folks, hold it down, Jessie's going.

1582
01:49:10,196 --> 01:49:11,663
Quiet.

1583
01:49:14,922 --> 01:49:17,686
- Goodbye, Jessie.
- See you on the other side, Jessie.

1584
01:49:17,890 --> 01:49:20,154
So long, Jessie!

1585
01:49:20,275 --> 01:49:21,632
Goodbye!

1586
01:49:27,166 --> 01:49:28,726
I'm sorry, Adam.

1587
01:49:30,002 --> 01:49:31,257
For what?

1588
01:49:33,148 --> 01:49:34,734
I'm just sorry.

1589
01:49:38,778 --> 01:49:40,382
Well, me too.

1590
01:49:41,366 --> 01:49:42,826
I'm sorry too.

1591
01:50:46,699 --> 01:50:48,976
You know the words to this song?

1592
01:50:49,636 --> 01:50:51,585
I think I heard it once before.

